---
// Problem — built to the literal structure of the BTF section in the visual ref:
//   • two vertical outline rules bracketing the content
//   • a clear inner grid with the text laid on top
//   • NO decorative cards/fragments
//   • thesis is one solid-ink text block with line breaks (no prism, no gradient text)
// COPY IS VERBATIM from Site structure.md.
import Container from './Container.astro';
---

<section class="relative border-t border-border-light bg-canvas-white">
  <Container class="px-0">
    <!-- two vertical outline rules + clear inner grid, text on top -->
    <div class="problem-panel dot-grid relative mx-auto max-w-[var(--width-narrow)] border-x border-border-light px-6 py-28 sm:px-12 sm:py-36 lg:px-20 lg:py-44">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-full">
        <h2 class="font-satoshi text-h1 text-logo-navy">
          Most adtech startups sound like everyone else in their category
        </h2>

        <div class="thesis mt-10 space-y-6 text-[clamp(1.125rem,2.1vw,1.5625rem)] font-medium leading-[1.5] tracking-[-0.01em] text-shadow-gray">
          <p>In doing so—they fail to give buyers any compelling reason for choosing them over the competition.</p>
          <p>Meanwhile, zero click is killing traffic, AI slop is clogging up every social feed, and buyers think they can vibe-code your replacement before the renewal date.</p>
          <p>Many adtech startups will fail to cross the chasm. And/or Labs was designed for the ones ready to leap.</p>
          <p>We blend GenAI, evidence-based frameworks, and a decade of battle-tested operator experience to help early-stage adtech startups outclass their competition.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</section>
